{"ts":"2026-06-27T03:59:03.919Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Component Design**\n\nI'm now refining the component suite design. I've decided on building a custom, modular system for `/app/portal/` and `/app/admin/`. We'll focus on a single table system or importable components under `@/components/private-app` that are well-designed. The primary focus is `PremiumDataTable`, with search, row click, mobile card fallback, and accessible keyboard navigation. These components will be applied across various sections like Projects, Documents, and Billing, ensuring a custom, premium aesthetic instead of standard HTML tables. I will use subtle hover effects, sticky headers and clean responsive cards on mobile. No backend calls.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T03:59:05.851Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing Interactive Components**\n\nI've been working on interactive components and have a clearer picture now. My design needs to include filters for status and type with sorting for keyboard accessibility. Hover states, and a premium EmptyState are critical. The table will have mobile card fallback, pagination, and keyboard navigation. I'm also planning the `DetailDrawer` with a blurred backdrop, rich data rendering, and micro-animations for interactive actions.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
