{"ts":"2026-06-27T04:00:26.300Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Verifying Motion Package**\n\nI've confirmed that the `motion` package, version 12.40.0, is installed, which is now the direct package name for the new Motion library, previously known as `framer-motion`. I'm going to explore Tailwind's simple transitions to start.\n\n\n**Prioritizing DataTable Design**\n\nI'm now focusing on designing the `PremiumDataTable`. I'm starting in `components/private-app/data-tables.tsx`. I want to ensure it looks modern and expensive. I'm exploring specific styling choices such as monospaced fonts, dark backdrop blur with subtle borders, status filters with interactive hover, keyboard-accessible sort headers, and mobile card layouts.\n\n\n**Designing Mobile Card Details**\n\nI'm now deep-diving into the mobile card design for the data table. I'm focusing on creating an accessible \"details\" drawer that's beautifully formatted. It'll use a fixed right-side drawer that slides in with a blur overlay and Escape key support for closure. I'm considering keyboard navigation too. I need to make sure the replacement is backward compatible. I'll thoroughly check the existing code at `./components/private-app/data-tables.tsx` before writing the code.\n\n\n**Refactoring DataTable Strategy**\n\nI've decided to refactor `DataTable` into a fully-featured `PremiumDataTable`. This approach ensures backward compatibility while exposing new functionalities. My plan involves making `DataTable` the upgraded component, retaining its basic interface while introducing properties like search (with `searchPlaceholder` and `searchKeys`), filter (using `categoryField`, `categories`, or status filters), row-clicking, and a mobile fallback. This elegantly upgrades existing implementations and provides fine-grained control.\n\n\n**Automating Mobile Card Design**\n\nI'm now focusing on a mobile-first approach for the data table. I'm exploring an automatic card layout on mobile if `mobileRender` is not provided. I'll make a default card renderer. I'm imagining a system where the first column becomes the card title, and other columns form a key-value grid within the card. This is looking elegant and fully automated! I will write a high-quality implementation of `DataTable` in `./components/private-app/data-tables.tsx` supporting search with the Lucide `Search` icon, and filter controls.\n\n\n**Implementing DataTable Features**\n\nI'm now implementing sortable headers with clear indicators and keyboard accessibility. I'm focusing on beautiful zebra/hover row styling with monospaced text. Pagination will be a clean control bar with item count and navigation. I'm also planning a sticky header option and a custom empty state rendering. I'm ensuring keyboard navigation, with tabIndex for rows, key down handlers, and a focus border.\n\\n\\n\nI'm also building the sliding detail drawer with a fixed right-side design, blurred overlay, and Escape key support for dismissal. It'll feature a key-value grid, a log stream, and action buttons.\n\n\n**Examining DataTable Context**\n\nI'm now determining all relevant files that require changes due to the data table enhancements. I'll focus on `./components/private-app/data-tables.tsx` first. I'm importing icons from `lucide-react`, and verified `lucide-react` is installed. I've confirmed that the upgraded `DataTable` must support both basic and advanced usage scenarios. I'm structuring the component with React hooks for state management.\n\n\n**Extending DataTable Capabilities**\n\nI'm now considering a standalone `DetailDrawer` component, exportable for independent use or as part of the `DataTable`. I'm refining `DataTable` properties to include custom renderers for drawer title and content. This will support actions and fine-tune rendering based on row data, extending the component's flexibility.\n\n\n**Defining DataTable Filters**\n\nI'm now focusing on implementing filtering within the `DataTable`. I'll support search queries against specified keys, and status/category filters via gorgeous tab and dropdown interfaces. The component will handle filtering and pagination automatically if `data` is passed. I've designed this to be fully backward-compatible.\n\n\n**Reviewing DataTable Implementation**\n\nI'm now implementing the interactive detail drawer for the data table. I'll include a header with title and ID, and a key-value list of the row's data. I'm also adding a mock eBPF log stream and action buttons. I've decided to examine the current file content of `./components/private-app/data-tables.tsx` to ensure backward compatibility.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T04:00:26.307Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"4z7r2wwb","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/components/private-app/data-tables.tsx","old_text":null,"new_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React, { useState, useEffect, useRef } from \"react\";\nimport { TableColumn } from \"./types\";\nimport { \n  Search, SlidersHorizontal, X, ChevronDown, RefreshCw, Download, \n  CheckCircle, ShieldCheck, Activity, FileText, Terminal, ArrowRight,\n  ChevronRight, Info, Lock, ArrowUpDown, ChevronUp, ChevronDown as ChevronDownIcon\n} from \"lucide-react\";\n\n// ==========================================\n// 1. DETAIL DRAWER COMPONENT (PREMIUM OVERLAY)\n// ==========================================\nexport interface DetailDrawerProps<T> {\n  isOpen: boolean;\n  onClose: () => void;\n  title: string;\n  row: T | null;\n  contentRenderer?: (row: T, onClose: () => void) => React.ReactNode;\n  actionsRenderer?: (row: T) => React.ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport function DetailDrawer<T extends { id: string | number }>({\n  isOpen,\n  onClose,\n  title,\n  row,\n  contentRenderer,\n  actionsRenderer\n}: DetailDrawerProps<T>) {\n  const [logs, setLogs] = useState<string[]>([]);\n  const [isSyncing, setIsSyncing] = useState(false);\n  const drawerRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);\n\n  // Close on Escape key press\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const handleKeyDown = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {\n      if (e.key === \"Escape\" && isOpen) {\n        onClose();\n      }\n    };\n    window.addEventListener(\"keydown\", handleKeyDown);\n    return () => window.removeEventListener(\"keydown\", handleKeyDown);\n  }, [isOpen, onClose]);\n\n  // Generate logs when drawer opens or row changes\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (isOpen && row) {\n      setLogs([\n        `[${new Date().toLocaleTimeString()}] INITIATING HARDWARE HANDSHAKE...`,\n        `[${new Date().toLocaleTimeString()}] COMPILING ENCLAVE POLICY REGISTER...`,\n        `[${new Date().toLocaleTimeString()}] RUNTIME VERIFICATION BOUNDARY: SHA-256 SECURED`,\n        `[${new Date().toLocaleTimeString()}] HARDWARE STATUS: 100% ISO-27001 COMPLIANT`\n      ]);\n    }\n  }, [isOpen, row]);\n\n  const handleSyncTelemetry = () => {\n    setIsSyncing(true);\n    setLogs(prev => [...prev, `[${new Date().toLocaleTimeString()}] REQUESTING eBPF KERNEL SYNC...`]);\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      setLogs(prev => [\n        ...prev,\n        `[${new Date().toLocaleTimeString()}] TELEMETRY PIPELINE SYNCED SUCCESSFULLY (0ms drift)`,\n        `[${new Date().toLocaleTimeString()}] ACTIVE SECURE STATE CONFIRMED`\n      ]);\n      setIsSyncing(false);\n    }, 1200);\n  };\n\n  if (!isOpen || !row) return null;\n\n  return (\n    <>\n      {/* Backdrop overlay */}\n      <div \n        className=\"fixed inset-0 bg-black/60 backdrop-blur-sm z-50 transition-opacity duration-300\"\n        onClick={onClose}\n        aria-hidden=\"true\"\n      />\n\n      {/* Sliding Panel */}\n      <div \n        ref={drawerRef}\n        role=\"dialog\"\n        aria-modal=\"true\"\n        aria-labelledby=\"drawer-title\"\n        className=\"fixed right-0 top-0 h-full w-full max-w-md bg-[#070708] border-l border-white/10 z-50 backdrop-blur-2xl p-6 shadow-[-12px_0_40px_rgba(0,0,0,0.85)] flex flex-col justify-between overflow-y-auto transition-transform duration-300 transform translate-x-0 font-mono text-[11.5px]\"\n      >\n        <div className=\"space-y-6 flex-1\">\n          {/* Header */}\n          <div className=\"flex justify-between items-start border-b border-white/5 pb-4\">\n            <div>\n              <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[#009DFF] mb-1\">\n                <ShieldCheck className=\"w-4 h-4\" />\n                <span className=\"text-[9px] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase\">ENCLAVE SECURE TERMINAL</span>\n              </div>\n              <h3 id=\"drawer-title\" className=\"text-[14px] font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-tight\">\n                {title}\n              </h3>\n              <p className=\"text-[9px] text-white/30 mt-0.5 uppercase tracking-wider\">\n                ID: {row.id} • Verified Sandbox\n              </p>\n            </div>\n            <button \n              onClick={onClose}\n              className=\"p-1 rounded hover:bg-white/5 text-white/50 hover:text-white transition-all cursor-pointer\"\n              aria-label=\"Close details drawer\"\n            >\n              <X className=\"w-4.5 h-4.5\" />\n            </button>\n          </div>\n\n          {/* Dynamic Content */}\n          <div className=\"space-y-5\">\n            {contentRenderer ? (\n              contentRenderer(row, onClose)\n            ) : (\n              /* Default high-fidelity structured key-value grid */\n              <div className=\"space-y-5\">\n                <div className=\"rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-white/[0.01] p-4 space-y-3\">\n                  <div className=\"text-[10px] font-bold text-white/40 uppercase tracking-widest border-b border-white/5 pb-1.5\">\n                    SPECIFICATION METRICS\n                  </div>\n                  <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-y-2.5 text-white/70\">\n                    {Object.entries(row)\n                      .filter(([key]) => key !== \"id\" && typeof row[key as keyof T] !== \"object\")\n                      .map(([key, val]) => (\n                        <React.Fragment key={key}>\n                          <div className=\"text-white/35 uppercase text-[10px]\">{key.replace(/([A-Z])/g, ' $1')}</div>\n                          <div className=\"text-right text-white font-semibold break-all\">\n                            {String(val) === \"true\" || String(val) === \"active\" || String(val) === \"stable\" || String(val) === \"verified\" || String(val) === \"compliant\" ? (\n                              <span className=\"text-emerald-400\">● {String(val).toUpperCase()}</span>\n                            ) : String(val) === \"warning\" || String(val) === \"critical\" ? (\n                              <span className=\"text-amber-400\">▲ {String(val).toUpperCase()}</span>\n                            ) : (\n                              String(val)\n                            )}\n                          </div>\n                        </React.Fragment>\n                      ))}\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n\n                {/* Diagnostics Live Console Stream */}\n                <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                  <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center text-[10px]\">\n                    <span className=\"text-white/40 font-bold uppercase tracking-widest\">DIAGNOSTIC TELEMETRY LOGS</span>\n                    <button \n                      onClick={handleSyncTelemetry}\n                      disabled={isSyncing}\n                      className=\"text-[#009DFF] hover:underline flex items-center gap-1 cursor-pointer disabled:opacity-40\"\n                    >\n                      <RefreshCw className={`w-3 h-3 ${isSyncing ? \"animate-spin\" : \"\"}`} />\n                      <span>RE-SYNC</span>\n                    </button>\n                  </div>\n                  <div className=\"p-3 rounded-lg bg-black border border-white/5 text-[9.5px] text-emerald-400/90 h-32 overflow-y-auto space-y-1 font-mono leading-relaxed\">\n                    {logs.map((log, idx) => (\n                      <div key={idx} className=\"border-l-2 border-emerald-500/20 pl-2\">\n                        {log}\n                      </div>\n                    ))}\n                    {isSyncing && (\n                      <div className=\"text-white/30 animate-pulse pl-2\">\n                        [SYNCING STATE ENCLAVE...]\n                      </div>\n                    )}\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            )}\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Action Panel at Bottom */}\n        <div className=\"pt-4 border-t border-white/5 flex flex-col gap-2 mt-4 shrink-0\">\n          {actionsRenderer ? (\n            actionsRenderer(row)\n          ) : (\n            <>\n              <button \n                onClick={() => alert(`Pulling certified ledger audit package for ${row.id}...`)}\n                className=\"w-full h-9 rounded bg-white hover:bg-white/90 text-black font-bold text-[10px] uppercase flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 transition-all cursor-pointer\"\n              >\n                <Download className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />\n                <span>Download Cryptographic Receipt</span>\n              </button>\n              <button \n                onClick={onClose}\n                className=\"w-full h-9 rounded border border-white/10 hover:bg-white/5 text-white/60 hover:text-white font-bold text-[10px] uppercase transition-all cursor-pointer\"\n              >\n                Close Secure Wire\n              </button>\n            </>\n          )}\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </>\n  );\n}\n\n\n// ==========================================\n// 2. MAIN PREMIUM DATA TABLE COMPONENT\n// ==========================================\nexport interface DataTableProps<T> {\n  columns: TableColumn<T>[];\n  data: T[];\n  pageSize?: number;\n  onRowClick?: (row: T) => void;\n  \n  // Advanced Filters\n  searchPlaceholder?: string;\n  searchKeys?: (keyof T | string)[];\n  statusField?: keyof T;\n  statusOptions?: string[];\n  categoryField?: keyof T;\n  categoryOptions?: string[];\n\n  // Custom detail drawer config\n  detailDrawerTitle?: (row: T) => string;\n  detailDrawerContent?: (row: T, onClose: () => void) => React.ReactNode;\n  detailDrawerActions?: (row: T) => React.ReactNode;\n  \n  // Extra formatting\n  stickyHeader?: boolean;\n}\n\nexport function DataTable<T extends { id: string | number }>({ \n  columns, \n  data, \n  pageSize = 5,\n  onRowClick,\n  searchPlaceholder = \"Search secure records...\",\n  searchKeys = [],\n  statusField,\n  statusOptions = [],\n  categoryField,\n  categoryOptions = [],\n  detailDrawerTitle,\n  detailDrawerContent,\n  detailDrawerActions,\n  stickyHeader = false\n}: DataTableProps<T>) {\n  const [currentPage, setCurrentPage] = useState(1);\n  const [sortKey, setSortKey] = useState<keyof T | string | null>(null);\n  const [sortOrder, setSortOrder] = useState<\"asc\" | \"desc\">(\"asc\");\n\n  // Filter States\n  const [searchQuery, setSearchQuery] = useState(\"\");\n  const [selectedStatus, setSelectedStatus] = useState(\"all\");\n  const [selectedCategory, setSelectedCategory] = useState(\"all\");\n\n  // Detail Drawer state\n  const [selectedRow, setSelectedRow] = useState<T | null>(null);\n  const [isDrawerOpen, setIsDrawerOpen] = useState(false);\n\n  // Dynamic filter lists compiled from data if not explicitly provided\n  const compiledStatusOptions = React.useMemo(() => {\n    if (statusOptions.length > 0) return statusOptions;\n    if (!statusField) return [];\n    const set = new Set(data.map(item => String(item[statusField]).toLowerCase()));\n    return Array.from(set);\n  }, [data, statusField, statusOptions]);\n\n  const compiledCategoryOptions = React.useMemo(() => {\n    if (categoryOptions.length > 0) return categoryOptions;\n    if (!categoryField) return [];\n    const set = new Set(data.map(item => String(item[categoryField]).toLowerCase()));\n    return Array.from(set);\n  }, [data, categoryField, categoryOptions]);\n\n  // Reset page when filters change\n  useEffect(() => {\n    setCurrentPage(1);\n  }, [searchQuery, selectedStatus, selectedCategory]);\n\n  const handleSort = (key: keyof T | string, sortable?: boolean) => {\n    if (!sortable) return;\n    if (sortKey === key) {\n      setSortOrder(sortOrder === \"asc\" ? \"desc\" : \"asc\");\n    } else {\n      setSortKey(key);\n      setSortOrder(\"asc\");\n    }\n  };\n\n  const handleRowSelect = (row: T) => {\n    if (onRowClick) {\n      onRowClick(row);\n    } else {\n      setSelectedRow(row);\n      setIsDrawerOpen(true);\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Keyboard navigation on row\n  const handleRowKeyDown = (e: React.KeyboardEvent, row: T) => {\n    if (e.key === \"Enter\" || e.key === \" \") {\n      e.preventDefault();\n      handleRowSelect(row);\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Filtering Logic\n  const filteredData = React.useMemo(() => {\n    return data.filter(item => {\n      // 1. Search Query\n      if (searchQuery.trim() !== \"\") {\n        const query = searchQuery.toLowerCase();\n        const keysToSearch = searchKeys.length > 0 \n          ? searchKeys \n          : Object.keys(item); // Default to search all fields if not specified\n\n        const matchesSearch = keysToSearch.some(key => {\n          const val = item[key as keyof T];\n          return val !== undefined && val !== null && String(val).toLowerCase().includes(query);\n        });\n\n        if (!matchesSearch) return false;\n      }\n\n      // 2. Status Filter\n      if (statusField && selectedStatus !== \"all\") {\n        if (String(item[statusField]).toLowerCase() !== selectedStatus.toLowerCase()) {\n          return false;\n        }\n      }\n\n      // 3. Category Filter\n      if (categoryField && selectedCategory !== \"all\") {\n        if (String(item[categoryField]).toLowerCase() !== selectedCategory.toLowerCase()) {\n          return false;\n        }\n      }\n\n      return true;\n    });\n  }, [data, searchQuery, searchKeys, statusField, selectedStatus, categoryField, selectedCategory]);\n\n  // Sorting Logic\n  const processedData = React.useMemo(() => {\n    const list = [...filteredData];\n    if (sortKey) {\n      list.sort((a, b) => {\n        const aVal = a[sortKey as keyof T];\n        const bVal = b[sortKey as keyof T];\n        \n        if (aVal === undefined || aVal === null) return 1;\n        if (bVal === undefined || bVal === null) return -1;\n\n        if (typeof aVal === \"number\" && typeof bVal === \"number\") {\n          return sortOrder === \"asc\" ? aVal - bVal : bVal - aVal;\n        }\n        \n        const aStr = String(aVal).toLowerCase();\n        const bStr = String(bVal).toLowerCase();\n        return sortOrder === \"asc\" ? aStr.localeCompare(bStr) : bStr.localeCompare(aStr);\n      });\n    }\n    return list;\n  }, [filteredData, sortKey, sortOrder]);\n\n  const totalPages = Math.ceil(processedData.length / pageSize) || 1;\n  const paginatedData = processedData.slice(\n    (currentPage - 1) * pageSize,\n    currentPage * pageSize\n  );\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"space-y-4\">\n      \n      {/* 1. FILTER & CONTROLS CONTROL PANEL */}\n      <div className=\"flex flex-col gap-3\">\n        <div className=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-3 items-stretch\">\n          {/* Search Bar */}\n          <div className=\"relative flex-grow\">\n            <Search className=\"absolute left-3.5 top-2.5 w-4 h-4 text-white/30 animate-pulse\" />\n            <input \n              type=\"text\"\n              value={searchQuery}\n              onChange={(e) => setSearchQuery(e.target.value)}\n              placeholder={searchPlaceholder}\n              className=\"w-full h-9.5 rounded-xl border border-white/5 bg-[#030304]/60 pl-10 pr-4 text-[12px] font-mono text-white placeholder-white/25 outline-none focus:border-[#009DFF]/30 focus:bg-white/[0.03] transition-all\"\n            />\n            {searchQuery && (\n              <button \n                onClick={() => setSearchQuery(\"\")}\n                className=\"absolute right-3 top-2.5 text-white/30 hover:text-white cursor-pointer\"\n                aria-label=\"Clear search\"\n              >\n                <X className=\"w-4 h-4\" />\n              </button>\n            )}\n          </div>\n\n          {/* Category Dropdown Filter */}\n          {categoryField && compiledCategoryOptions.length > 0 && (\n            <div className=\"relative shrink-0 min-w-[160px]\">\n              <select \n                value={selectedCategory}\n                onChange={(e) => setSelectedCategory(e.target.value)}\n                className=\"w-full h-9.5 rounded-xl border border-white/5 bg-[#030304]/60 hover:bg-white/[0.03] px-4 pr-10 text-[11px] font-mono text-white/70 focus:text-white outline-none transition-all cursor-pointer appearance-none uppercase\"\n              >\n                <option value=\"all\">ALL CATEGORIES</option>\n                {compiledCategoryOptions.map((cat) => (\n                  <option key={cat} value={cat}>{cat.replace(\"_\", \" \")}</option>\n                ))}\n              </select>\n              <ChevronDown className=\"absolute right-3.5 top-3 w-3.5 h-3.5 text-white/45 pointer-events-none\" />\n            </div>\n          )}\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Status Horizontal Tabs Filter */}\n        {statusField && compiledStatusOptions.length > 0 && (\n          <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 overflow-x-auto pb-1.5 select-none scrollbar-none border-b border-white/5\">\n            <button\n              onClick={() => setSelectedStatus(\"all\")}\n              className={`h-7 px-3 rounded-lg text-[9.5px] font-mono font-bold tracking-wider uppercase transition-all cursor-pointer ${\n                selectedStatus === \"all\" \n                  ? \"bg-[#009DFF]/10 text-[#009DFF] border border-[#009DFF]/25\" \n                  : \"bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/5 text-white/50 hover:text-white hover:bg-white/[0.04]\"\n              }`}\n            >\n              ALL SYSTEMS\n            </button>\n            {compiledStatusOptions.map((status) => (\n              <button\n                key={status}\n                onClick={() => setSelectedStatus(status)}\n                className={`h-7 px-3 rounded-lg text-[9.5px] font-mono font-bold tracking-wider uppercase transition-all cursor-pointer ${\n                  selectedStatus === status \n                    ? \"bg-[#009DFF]/15 text-[#009DFF] border border-[#009DFF]/30\" \n                    : \"bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/5 text-white/50 hover:text-white hover:bg-white/[0.04]\"\n                }`}\n              >\n                {status.replace(\"_\", \" \")}\n              </button>\n            ))}\n          </div>\n        )}\n      </div>\n\n      {/* 2. ULTIMATE DESKTOP TABULAR VIEW */}\n      <div className=\"hidden md:block border border-white/5 rounded-xl overflow-hidden bg-[#040405]/35 backdrop-blur-md\">\n        <div className=\"overflow-x-auto\">\n          <table className=\"w-full text-left font-mono text-[11px] text-white/70 table-layout-fixed\">\n            <thead>\n              <tr className={`bg-white/[0.015] border-b border-white/5 text-white/40 text-[9.5px] uppercase select-none ${stickyHeader ? \"sticky top-0 z-10 backdrop-blur-xl\" : \"\"}`}>\n                {columns.map((col, idx) => (\n                  <th \n                    key={idx} \n                    onClick={() => handleSort(col.key, col.sortable)}\n                    onKeyDown={(e) => col.sortable && (e.key === \"Enter\" || e.key === \" \") && (e.preventDefault(), handleSort(col.key, true))}\n                    tabIndex={col.sortable ? 0 : -1}\n                    className={`p-4 font-bold tracking-wider focus:outline-none focus:bg-white/[0.03] ${col.sortable ? \"hover:text-white cursor-pointer\" : \"\"}`}\n                    aria-sort={sortKey === col.key ? (sortOrder === \"asc\" ? \"ascending\" : \"descending\") : undefined}\n                  >\n                    <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n                      <span>{col.header}</span>\n                      {col.sortable && (\n                        sortKey === col.key ? (\n                          <span className=\"text-[#009DFF]\">\n                            {sortOrder === \"asc\" ? <ChevronUp className=\"w-3 h-3 inline\" /> : <ChevronDownIcon className=\"w-3 h-3 inline\" />}\n                          </span>\n                        ) : (\n                          <ArrowUpDown className=\"w-3 h-3 text-white/20 hover:text-white/45 inline transition-colors\" />\n                        )\n                      )}\n                    </div>\n                  </th>\n                ))}\n              </tr>\n            </thead>\n            <tbody className=\"divide-y divide-white/5\">\n              {paginatedData.length === 0 ? (\n                <tr>\n                  <td colSpan={columns.length} className=\"p-10 text-center text-white/35 font-mono text-[11px]\">\n                    <div className=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-2 max-w-sm mx-auto\">\n                      <Info className=\"w-7 h-7 text-[#009DFF]/60 animate-bounce\" />\n                      <span className=\"font-bold text-white uppercase text-[11.5px] tracking-wider mt-1\">NO TELEMETRY RECORD MATCHED</span>\n                      <p className=\"text-[10px] text-white/40 leading-relaxed\">Adjust your active parameters or check back within the sovereign sandbox.</p>\n                    </div>\n                  </td>\n                </tr>\n              ) : (\n                paginatedData.map((row, rIdx) => (\n                  <tr \n                    key={row.id || rIdx} \n                    onClick={() => handleRowSelect(row)}\n                    onKeyDown={(e) => handleRowKeyDown(e, row)}\n                    tabIndex={0}\n                    className=\"group transition-all hover:bg-white/[0.015] focus:bg-white/[0.025] focus:outline-none cursor-pointer relative\"\n                  >\n                    {columns.map((col, cIdx) => (\n                      <td key={cIdx} className=\"p-4 leading-normal font-medium\">\n                        {col.render ? col.render(row) : (\n                          String(row[col.key as keyof T]) === \"true\" || String(row[col.key as keyof T]) === \"active\" || String(row[col.key as keyof T]) === \"stable\" || String(row[col.key as keyof T]) === \"verified\" || String(row[col.key as keyof T]) === \"compliant\" ? (\n                            <span className=\"px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[9px] font-bold bg-green-500/10 text-green-400 border border-green-500/20 uppercase tracking-wide\">\n                              {String(row[col.key as keyof T])}\n                            </span>\n                          ) : String(row[col.key as keyof T]) === \"warning\" || String(row[col.key as keyof T]) === \"critical\" ? (\n                            <span className=\"px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[9px] font-bold bg-amber-500/10 text-amber-400 border border-amber-500/20 uppercase tracking-wide\">\n                              {String(row[col.key as keyof T])}\n                            </span>\n                          ) : (\n                            row[col.key as keyof T] as React.ReactNode\n                          )\n                        )}\n                      </td>\n                    ))}\n                  </tr>\n                ))\n              )}\n            </tbody>\n          </table>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      {/* 3. PREMIUM MOBILE CARD FALLBACK VIEW */}\n      <div className=\"block md:hidden space-y-3.5\">\n        {paginatedData.length === 0 ? (\n          <div className=\"border border-white/5 rounded-xl bg-[#040405]/35 p-8 text-center text-white/35 font-mono\">\n            <Info className=\"w-6 h-6 text-[#009DFF]/60 mx-auto mb-2\" />\n            <span className=\"font-bold text-white uppercase text-[11px] tracking-widest\">NO DATA RECORDS</span>\n            <p className=\"text-[10px] text-white/40 mt-1\">No matching nodes exist within sandbox boundary.</p>\n          </div>\n        ) : (\n          paginatedData.map((row, rIdx) => (\n            <div \n              key={row.id || rIdx}\n              onClick={() => handleRowSelect(row)}\n              className=\"border border-white/5 rounded-xl bg-[#040405]/35 p-4 space-y-3 font-mono text-[11px] hover:bg-white/[0.015] active:bg-white/[0.03] transition-all cursor-pointer\"\n            >\n              <div className=\"flex justify-between items-start border-b border-white/5 pb-2\">\n                <div>\n                  <span className=\"text-[10px] text-[#009DFF] font-bold tracking-wider uppercase\">\n                    ID: {row.id}\n                  </span>\n                  <h4 className=\"text-white font-bold uppercase mt-1 text-[11.5px] max-w-[200px] truncate\">\n                    {/* Primary Identifier (matches first column's content) */}\n                    {String(row[columns[0].key as keyof T] || row.id)}\n                  </h4>\n                </div>\n                {/* Find status fields if any to draw badges */}\n                {statusField && (\n                  <span className={`px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[9px] font-bold border uppercase tracking-wider ${\n                    String(row[statusField]).toLowerCase().includes(\"active\") || String(row[statusField]).toLowerCase().includes(\"stable\") || String(row[statusField]).toLowerCase().includes(\"verified\") || String(row[statusField]).toLowerCase().includes(\"compliant\")\n                      ? \"bg-green-500/10 text-green-400 border-green-500/20\"\n                      : String(row[statusField]).toLowerCase().includes(\"warning\") || String(row[statusField]).toLowerCase().includes(\"critical\")\n                      ? \"bg-amber-500/10 text-amber-400 border-amber-500/20\"\n                      : \"bg-white/5 text-white/50 border-white/10\"\n                  }`}>\n                    {String(row[statusField])}\n                  </span>\n                )}\n              </div>\n\n              {/* Sub-details grid inside the card */}\n              <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-2 gap-y-1.5 text-[10px] text-white/50\">\n                {columns.slice(1, 4).map((col, cIdx) => (\n                  <div key={cIdx} className=\"space-y-0.5\">\n                    <span className=\"text-[8.5px] text-white/30 uppercase tracking-widest block\">{col.header}</span>\n                    <span className=\"text-white/80 font-medium truncate block max-w-[150px]\">\n                      {col.render ? col.render(row) : String(row[col.key as keyof T] || \"-\")}\n                    </span>\n                  </div>\n                ))}\n              </div>\n\n              {/* Action link */}\n              <div className=\"pt-2 border-t border-white/5 flex justify-between items-center text-[9px] text-[#009DFF] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider\">\n                <span>View Full Core Details</span>\n                <ChevronRight className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          ))\n        )}\n      </div>\n\n      {/* 4. PREMIUM COMPOSITE PAGINATION CONTROLS */}\n      {totalPages > 1 && (\n        <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center bg-[#030304]/30 border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-3 select-none font-mono text-[10px]\">\n          <span className=\"text-white/35 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider\">\n            PAGE {currentPage} OF {totalPages} ({processedData.length} CORE ENTITIES)\n          </span>\n          <div className=\"flex gap-1.5\">\n            <button \n              disabled={currentPage === 1}\n              onClick={() => setCurrentPage(p => Math.max(1, p - 1))}\n              className=\"px-2.5 h-7 rounded border border-white/5 text-[9.5px] text-white font-bold tracking-wider hover:bg-white/5 disabled:opacity-20 transition-all cursor-pointer disabled:cursor-not-allowed\"\n            >\n              PREV\n            </button>\n            <button \n              disabled={currentPage === totalPages}\n              onClick={() => setCurrentPage(p => Math.min(totalPages, p + 1))}\n              className=\"px-2.5 h-7 rounded border border-white/5 text-[9.5px] text-white font-bold tracking-wider hover:bg-white/5 disabled:opacity-20 transition-all cursor-pointer disabled:cursor-not-allowed\"\n            >\n              NEXT\n            </button>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      {/* 5. SLIDING OVERLAY DRAWER */}\n      <DetailDrawer \n        isOpen={isDrawerOpen}\n        onClose={() => setIsDrawerOpen(false)}\n        title={selectedRow ? (detailDrawerTitle ? detailDrawerTitle(selectedRow) : String(selectedRow[columns[0].key as keyof T] || selectedRow.id)) : \"\"}\n        row={selectedRow}\n        contentRenderer={detailDrawerContent ? (row, close) => detailDrawerContent(row, close) : undefined}\n        actionsRenderer={detailDrawerActions ? (row) => detailDrawerActions(row) : undefined}\n      />\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n"}}}
